# Structural Context

Structural context is available at `{{.StructuralContextPath}}`. Read it first. It may include CodeGraph-derived symbols, entry points, modules, and call/dependency clues. Use it to identify high-signal files and directories before inspecting the full candidate list.

Do not linearly read the complete candidate file list when structural context is enough to identify the relevant analysis scope. Read candidate metadata or candidate paths only to verify proposed files, fill missing adjacent candidates, or resolve uncertainty.
